-- Putin Regrets Annan’s Resignation as Syria Envoy, Interfax Says
-- B y   Y u l i y a   F e d o r i n o v a
-- 2012-08-02T18:09:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-02/putin-regrets-annan-s-resignation-as-syria-envoy-interfax-says.html
Russia’s President Vladimir Putin
said he regrets the departure of  Kofi Annan  as the United
Nations’ special enjoy to Syria, Interfax reported, citing Putin
as saying in London today.  Putin said Annan is “a very decent man and brilliant
diplomat,” according to Interfax.  Separately, Putin said Russia and the U.K. are discussing
cooperation in the space industry and in the military-technical
field, Interfax said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Yuliya Fedorinova in Moscow at 
 yfedorinova@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
